text: Clay County is a county in the U.S. state of Missouri. As of the 2020 census, the county had a population of 253,335, making it the fifth-most populous county in Missouri. The county seat is Liberty. It was founded on January 2, 1822. == References == Category:1820s establishments in Missouri Category:1822 establishments in the United States Category:Missouri counties
title: Clay County, Missouri
